3. What are "Decision Metaphors"? Name a few.
Decision Metaphors are different ways to represent business logic visually. Common ones include:

Decision Tables: Best for logic with many conditions leading to specific actions.
Decision Trees: Best for hierarchical, branching logic.
Scorecards: Used for calculating a cumulative score based on weighted attributes (common in credit risk).
Rule Flows: Define the sequence or order in which different rule sets are executed.
